title: The Bus
description: When Rocky suggests the Elmore Junior High kids skip school, the bus is boarded by criminals, who seem to want to teach them the importance of school attendance. The masked culprits are clearly the children's parents faking a heist to teach them a lesson. But when the police get involved for real, it becomes clear the parents aren't the ones pulling the strings.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Telly
description: Grady thinks the TV show they are watching is awful and decides to get the gang together to make their own show.

title: The Compilation
description: A compilation of some of the funniest, most bizarre clips uploaded onto the internet by the people of Elmore. Clips include Banana Joe's self-choreographed acrobatics, Richard's latest culinary invention and Gumball and Darwin's contest for who can pull the weirdest face.

title: Clayton
description: Darwin needs to find a photo of Clayton to put on the cover of the school yearbook - but he makes the mistake of seeking help from Tobias, who has his eye on the cover spot himself! Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: The Box
description: The Wattersons receive an unmarked package in the mail. To distract themselves from the urge to open it they all take turns to imagine what it might contain. To Mom it could mean financial freedom, to Gumball it could mean superpowers; to whoever it's actually for, it means they're not getting their package.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Weird Food
description: Puppet Gumball imagines some weird food then tries it.

title: The Hero
description: Gumball and Darwin are determined to prove to their dad that he is their hero, at any cost!

title: Sarah
description: Darwin asks Sarah for a photo to put on the cover of the school yearbook. But when Sarah tries to help, things get a little sticky. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: Teachers
description: When Darwin asks his friends which teacher deserves to be on the yearbook cover, they struggle to find a single worthy candidate! Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: The Cycle
description: Gumball, Darwin and Anais discover that Mr Wilson has been picking on their Dad for most of his life; ever since he humiliated Richard with a high school prank. The kids try to work Dad through it but when their efforts fail, they realize that getting back at Mr Wilson is the only way to break the cycle.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Spoons
description: Frank has taken Grady's beloved house Spoon. Grady is forced into a dance off to win it back.

title: Alan
description: Darwin wants to put Alan on the cover of the school yearbook - but Alan's apparent modesty gets in the way. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: The Buddy
description: Anais and school psycho Jamie are accused of the same techno-crime. They are forced to team up to discover the real culprit in order to prove their innocence. After solving the case, they realize that they have more in common than they thought...

title: Banana Joe
description: When Principal Brown sets Darwin the task of making the school yearbook, Darwin starts by asking class clown Banana Joe for a simple selfie to put on the cover. But with Banana Joe, things are never that simple. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Pineapple
description: Gumball briefly loses his puppet mouth to an enthusiastic Pineapple.

title: The Words
description: Darwin is too polite to speak his mind, so Gumball teaches him to be direct via an epic battle of insults.

title: Waiting for Gumball: BirdPlaneBird
description: Darwin and BirdPlaneBird try to share a refreshing drink, it turns out to be hard as a puppet.

title: The Grades
description: Miss Simian discovers a failed test from Gumball's past that brings down his grade point average. This means he has to retake kindergarten all over again, much to her delight. But by demoting him Miss Simian has inadvertently brought herself down, and they're left with no choice but to team up if they want things back to normal.

title: The World
description: The amazing world of Elmore is full of inanimate objects that aren't nearly as inanimate as you might hope!

title: Waiting for Gumball: Insulting Voices
description: Gumball and Darwin play with smaller hand puppets of themselves who mimic their voices very badly.

title: The Detective
description: Anais arrives in the bedroom to find a messy crime-scene and her Daisy doll missing. She realizes Gumball and Darwin are the chief suspects. Following a series of clues is her only chance to track them down and her only hope of learning what happened to Daisy. But as the mystery unravels, it seems the culprits may have turned on each other.

title: The Copycats
description: Gumball and Darwin are confused when they meet Kiki and Quack, a pair of siblings that copy everything they do and say. Then they find out this copycat family is making money online from imitating the Watterson family! When they fail to encourage them to find their own identity, the Wattersons realize they need a more permanent solution.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Infinite Loop
description: Gumball and Darwin discover smaller hand puppet  versions of themselves and get caught in an infinite loop of puppets.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Clean
description: Grady is determined to tidy up the house and persuades Howdy and Frank to help. While cleaning Frank unexpectedly discovers the love of his life under a bin bag.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Cool to Be Felt
description: Gumball and Darwin realize they are puppets and it's seriously cool.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Bored
description: Frank is bored and pesters the others to entertain him for the afternoon.

title: Carrie
description: Darwin sets out to find a photo of Carrie for the cover of the school yearbook - but they end up reminiscing about all their past spooky shenanigans. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: The Deal
description: When Mom wins Employee of the Month at the Rainbow factory, Richard feels like he is never celebrated for all the work he does at home. Nicole is suspicious of how much he actually does, but when Richard goes on strike, his important role in keeping things under control becomes painfully clear...

title: The Ad
description: To make ends meet, the Wattersons are forced to rent out their house. However, with nowhere else to stay they decide to secretly remain at the house. When they accidentally surprise their guests, an elderly pair of fainting goats, they faint...unsurprisingly.  The Wattersons fear the worst and attempt to cover up this "accident".

title: The Best
description: No matter what Gumball does, Carmen thinks she knows better. Gumball attempts to gain the moral high ground but fails spectacularly.  He decides that self-improvement isn't his style. The only option he has left is to bring Carmen down to his level.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Gnomes
description: Gumball and Darwin realize that anything they imagine will become real in Puppet World, but all they can think of are Garden Gnomes.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Beards
description: Puppet Gumball and Darwin discover they can grow very weird beards.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Grump
description: Frank is getting grumpy waiting for Gumball and Darwin to return so Grady and Howdy throw a party to cheer him up.

title: The Girlfriend
description: Jamie has decided she needs a sweetheart and, unlucky for him, she has decided Darwin is the best candidate.
